{
  "$comment": "Voice line script for Hedgemony hoglet/hedgehog/builder units. One source of truth for both the runtime registry and the batch generation script. Each unit/intent ships a baseline `lines` array plus per-fun-mode `lines_pirate` and `lines_lolcat` arrays aligned by index. Generate 2-4 takes per line for variety.",
  "voice_direction": {
    "tone": "Earnest, slightly anxious British radio operator. Think WW2 RAF dispatcher crossed with a small woodland creature. Never bombastic. Never sarcastic.",
    "tone_pirate": "Cornish/RP pirate hybrid. Drop the final 'g' on gerunds, lean on nautical verbs, sprinkle 'cap'n'. Keep the same anxious-helpful core energy — the hoglet is in costume, not a new personality.",
    "tone_lolcat": "Read literally and deadpan. The joke is the text vs. the earnest delivery. No cat-affected yowls, no cute voice. Stretching vowels is fine where the spelling implies it ('yuuus?'), but only as much as the spelling on the page.",
    "pace": "Quick. Most lines under 1.5 seconds.",
    "compression": "Light radio-band EQ + subtle bandpass for unit chatter; full range for the hedgehog (orchestrator) and goal-complete fanfare.",
    "loudness": "Normalize to -16 LUFS integrated; peak ceiling -2 dBTP. Trim leading/trailing silence to <50ms.",
    "format": "ogg vorbis, 44.1kHz, mono. Filename: <unit>_<intent>_<index>.ogg (e.g. hoglet_select_01.ogg)."
  },
